                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                                                        Bopanna retained, Yuki in  Calcutta: Yuki Bhambri found a place in the Indian Davis Cup squad for the crucial World Group play-off tie against South Africa from September 18-20.
  The All India Tennis Association (AITA) brought in Yuki in place of Sanam Singh, who was a reserve player for India against Chinese Taipei, in the squad, which otherwise remained unchanged.  Leander Paes, Mahesh Bhupathi, Somdev Dev Varman and Rohan Bopanna, are the other members of the squad. SP Misra will continue as the non-playing captain while Nandan Bal will be coach.  Nadal included  Seville: World No. 3 Rafael Nadal has been included in Spain rsquo;s squad for their Davis Cup World Group semi-final against Israel next week despite problems with an apparent stomach injury at the US Open.  David Ferrer, Tommy Robredo and Feliciano Lopez make up the defending champions rsquo; team for the three-day tie against Israel in Murcia, starting on September 18, coach Francis Roig said at a news conference in Seville.  Radcliffe back  London: Paula Radcliffe will race in the world half-marathon championships on October 11, after being named in the British team for the Birmingham event, UK Athletics said on Tuesday.  Rossi plan  Milan: MotoGP world champion Valentino Rossi has not completely ruled out racing for Ferrari in Formula One in future. The Italian considered joining Ferrari three years ago, but eventually stuck to bikes.   Hair honour  Sydney: Darrell Hair has been honoured with life membership of his Australian state association mdash; New South Wales mdash; the year after he was reinstated as an international umpire following a suspension for presiding over the first forfeit in Test cricket.   Broad rested  London: Stuart Broad will miss England rsquo;s third one-day International against Australia at the Rose Bowl Wednesday because of a neck strain, an ECB release said Tuesday.  Azhar view  Bhopal: Former India captain Mohammed Azharuddin Tuesday criticised the selectors rsquo; decision to bring Rahul Dravid back in the ODI squad and said that a youngster should have been preferred instead.  Trophy partner  Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) in a release, on Tuesday, has announced Hero Honda Motors Ltd as global partner for the upcoming ICC Champions Trophy 2009 scheduled from September 22 to October 5.   
